{"cursor":"5414","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Multiple issues\n| refimprove = November 2011 out of date = November 2011\n}}\n\nThe 'inheritance of acquired characteristics' is a hypothesis that physiological\nchanges acquired over the life of an organism (such as the enlargement of a\nmuscle through repeated use) may be transmitted to offspring. It is also\ncommonly referred to as the 'theory of [[adaptation]]' equated with the\nevolutionary theory of French naturalist Jean-Baptiste Lamarck known as\n[[Lamarckism]].\n","linknr":178,"url":"Inheritance_of_acquired_characteristics","recorded":1362486429,"links":30,"instances":["psychologist"],"pdf":["http://jeb.biologists.org/cgi/reprint/31/3/307.pdf","http://www.ias.ac.in/jarch/jgenet/33/61.pdf","http://jeb.biologists.org/cgi/reprint/31/3/307.pdf","http://www.ias.ac.in/jarch/jgenet/33/61.pdf"],"categories":["History of ideas","History of biology","Evolutionary biology","Genetics"],"headings":["History","See also","Citations","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Ambox_outdated_content.svg/42px-Ambox_outdated_content.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Jean-Baptiste_Lamarck.jpg/220px-Jean-Baptiste_Lamarck.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/89/Symbol_book_class2.svg/16px-Symbol_book_class2.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["william_mcdougall","psychologist"]],"members":["william_mcdougall"],"related":["Muscle","France","Natural_history","Jean-Baptiste_Lamarck","Hippocrate